Text.string: Very good. That is the third and final Vault Key fragment. Bring it to me on Sanctuary, and I will assemble the full Key.
Good, you're here. Bring that Key fragment to my lab.
We'll have to be fast. We go in through the skyway by vehicle.
It mentions a “Vault of Vaults” and “the setting of the moon”. Could that be the Great Vault Tyreen Calypso has been promising her followers?

Eridian writing is the most complex poetry in the universe. The relative position of one sentence to another can change the meanings of both completely. These symbols are placed like a diagram. What do they represent?

I've got it! Each symbol describes the sidereal coordinates of a Vault on a different planet! That one in the left is the Promethean Vault, while the central symbol is Pandora. If they're connected somehow, that explains why Tyreen wanted the map so badly.

Fascinating! This Vault is linked by an ancient energy conduit to a second Vault. Those coordinates look like... Eden-6! Good work, Vault Hunter. We have our next destination! Collect Maya and her little truant and return to the ship.
That portal is marked with the Eridian symbol for “Guardians”. See what lies beyond it.
By just ditching me on the ship?! You said I could be a Vault Hunter like you! You promised!
You will! When you're ready.
What's up, bitches? Ohhhh, Troy! Look what they left for us!
Thanks for doing all the hard work. Man, you Vault Thieves only think with your trigger fingers, huh?
Keep this up and I'll be a god for real!
Got it. I'll take point with the Vault Hunter.
Uh—WE'LL be gods.
That's what I said. Now... let me do my thing.
No! What are you doing?!
Woah, that thing is ugly! And it's still breathing! That's so cool!
Hey. Save any for the “parasite”?
We're leaving. Now.
We SHOULD be kicking their asses!
So who's the brat? You I get, but what's her deal?
She's no one. I'm your problem.
I'm gonna be a Siren, and then I'm gonna mop the floor with assholes like you!
This one's mine. We're opening a Vault, Maya. You expect me to miss that? I can handle myself, Siren or not.
You're gonna... pahaha! Is that how you think this works? Honey, you're not even gonna leave this place.
Put her down!
To the badass goes the loot.
Time to get my well-earned reward.
And now, the spoils of the hunt.
Let's loot this sucker!
Maya!
This place must be, like... a hundred years old. Maybe even TWO hundred!
NO!
I thought you could only take from me.
I guess it's... any Siren.
Come on. We got what we came for.
Yeah. And a lot more.
Lilith, we don't know what's down there. It could get ugly! You brought me back to the Raiders for a reason. You're the commander. Use the weapons you've got.
The Vault Map led us here for a reason. There must be some significance to this device.
She's dead. Maya's dead.
Come on. Let's get the hell out of here.
We're not safe here. Come with me.
We can mourn when we are safe. Come with me.
Lass, we've got to go.
Sorry, Vault Hunter. There was nothing you could do. Thanks for getting Ava back safely.
I'm sure they're gettin' ready for the jump to Eden-6. You should be up there. I think I need to be alone for a little bit.
Ava. I'm trying to keep you safe.
Taking what's ours. See, the monsters don't protect the power of the Vaults. They ARE the power of the Vaults.
And now it's all mine.
Slag me, you're really openin' up the Vault? Good luck! And whatever you find in there... try not to lead it back to the city.
Aghhhrghhrgh!
But hey, if that Siren thing ever works out for you...
Heyyy id—oh, heh. Looks like we interrupted your sadtimes. Um, here! Maybe this'll cheer you up.
Right? Ah, memories. Our followers love it! Recruitment is skyrocketing!
Man, your dead Siren's powers are amazeballs! Woo! I've been phaselockin' grapes and tossin' 'em into my mouth all day! Oh, uhp—mm! Your friend's dead!
Always a step behind, eh, Lil? Welp, see ya at the next Vault! Which totally doesn't rhyme with “smheeden-shmix”. Byeee!
Trust me, I asked the Vault Hunter. It was the right decision and I'm sticking with it. Morale's at an all time high!
There you are. We were just talking... mustaches, hopefully for the last time.
So what's the plan, commander?
Yeah.
See you planet-side, Vault Hunter.
Daggertooth clan, this one was practically made for you.
Lilith! We're runnin' out of road!
The Vault is close now. Whatever power is inside, the Eridians locked it away for a reason. You must not let the Calypsos acquire it for themselves.
Ava... we need to talk.
Uh huh, uh huh. Yeah.
This isn't a joke!
Yeah-yeah-yeah, I know. For sure.
Don't touch anything.
I'm probably not.
We have a lot to unpack here. Collect Maya and her little truant and return to the ship.
[sigh] Okay. This one's all you.
That's what I thought.
Ava! Don't!
Be... ready...
Maya... she's gone. Grab the girl and get back to the ship. I'll... tell Lilith.
Vault Hunter. We're on the bridge.

Lilith. You have to say something.||Fine, I'll say something. I knew Maya when she was alive. I preferred her that way. That didn't come out right, but... she's gone, and that's how it is. All we can do is fight to honor her memory the best we can. People die in wars. By the droves. I mean, open your eyes, people.||—Don't ask me to speak at your funeral, Lilith.
Heh. No kidding, Tannis.

I never “kid”. I know what I am: a brilliantly ruthless scientist. And you know what you are, because everyone on this ship is waiting for you to say something—and they won't be able to get back to the very important things they need to do to keep this hunk of floating space debris functioning until you do.

Maya wasn't just a Crimson Raider, or a Vault Hunter. She was family. But we can't lose sight of our mission. We're going to open the Vaults. That's how we make her death mean... anything. Everyone back to your stations.
“Open the Vaults”? That's all you have to say?! Maya's DEAD because you wanted to open the Vaults. We SHOULD be hunting down the Calypsos and making them PAY for what they did!
Next Vault, we do it together. Once you've got your wings back.
It's... not that easy.
Maya always told me a Vault Hunter runs TOWARD the fire. All her stories were about you! You saved Pandora! You killed Handsome Jack! You're SUPPOSED to be the Firehawk!
I... I don't know what I am.
FIGURE IT OUT, Lilith! Before you get someone else killed!
Vault Hunter. Go see if she's all right, will you? I'll... get us ready for the jump to Eden-6.
Oh. Hey, Vault Hunter. Not much to say, you know, it's a war. People die.
Yeah, they do that. But you're still here. And the war's not over.
Yeah, you're right. Doesn't make it any easier. But Maya put her faith in you for a reason, huh? Keep fighting. Make her proud.
As they must. But do not fear Death. She is a friend who welcomes you at the end of your hunt.
Someday, when you're old enough, we'll get absolutely shitefaced and sing songs about her till our throats go hoarse.
Thanks. You didn't have to come talk to me, but... I'm glad you did. Here, this is... it was hers. She'd probably want you to have it.
Vault Hunter—good, you're here. We need to set a course to Eden-6. No time to waste.
Lilith! Incoming transmission!
All right, Maya—let's gear up. First Vault, what should I bring?
What now?
I'm not sure those monsters care about anyone or anything. And that's what makes them so dangerous.
It's hurt! Hit it with everything you've got!
It's injured! Hit it hard!
Now's our chance! Light this thing up!
Crap, it's invulnerable!
It's not taking any damage!
I can't make a dent in that thing!
Holy crap, this place is gettin' wrecked!
Hope that wasn't load-bearing!
That thing is knocking the place down!
Watch out! That thing is transforming!
What is HAPPENING to that thing?
It's turning into... even more of a monster?!
Shoot those things!
I don't know what those are, but we should probably shoot them!
Shoot those glowing things!
(choke react)
(choked into fall react)
(hit react)
Nope. Stay with Lilith.
(struggle)
(land react)
(crawling)
(straining)
Ghhh.
(strain)
(strain)
(effort)
(thrown back, superhero landing)
(phaselock react)
Yes yes, good job saving lives or whatever. Now, place the final Key fragment on the charging device, right over there.
Seriously?! What have I been training for? I'm ready, Maya.
(punch effort, catch)
(punch react)
(grappled effort)
(leech effort)
(leech react)
(pulls gun)
(phaselock effort)
Not yet.
Ava. I could use some help up here on the bridge. You want to take comms?
Yeah, no, I'm good.
All right, killer. Apollyon Station's the last stop on the central line. Take the central arterial highway out of the city.
Heads up, a, uh, squad of Maliwan holdouts have fortified the access ramp. You'll have to kick them out if you want to get through. I'm sending Atlas forces that-a-way to support you!
You read my mind, Rhys. Vault Hunter, secure the ramp and push through.

What's up, chucklenuts? It's been a grip. So life update: Katagawa shat the bed, but you knew that already. Troy's whining that we haven't opened the Vault yet, and I can't get properly laid because I keep leeching my partners to death, so... that's my whole thing. Oh, you're busy! It's cool. But let's catch up real soon, 'kay?
These soldiers fight on, / though their leader has been killed. / Honor them with death.
The Vault's hidden beneath the city? How did no one ever find it?
There's a Vault underneath the city? And no one ever found it?
A Vault, hidden beneath the city? How has this remained a secret?
There's a bloody Vault right under the city? How'd you keep that under wraps?
Now, shoo. I need to do a lot of science and your natural odor is alluringly potent, and thus distracting.
They made for short work. / Atlas reigns victorious. / Join me, Vault Hunter.
Heya, badass. You ready to crack open that Vault?
10-4. Let's do this thing.
That's why I'm here!
Hells to the yes. Did I use that right?
Course! What the hell am I doing here otherwise?
Yo Ellie, we'd like to make it to the Vault in one piece. What you got for me?
Girl, I've been waitin' for you to say something like that. Get ready for Project Double-D!
You seek the highway. / I will clear the path for you. / Cool swords are handy.
Hell yeah. Oh, Ellie. Never change.
You're drivin'. Need my hands free!
We need some tunes! Let's see what Ellie's got on here.
Classic.
Crimson Raiders to the bridge.
Hey, superfan! What's the hurry? Going somewhere important? You wouldn't mind if I, I dunno, broadcast your location to every maniac on the planet? No? You sure? Cool, I was gonna do it anyway.
Don't worry about her, we got this. Just like on Athenas, right?

Whaaaat is up my brothers and sisters! Impromptu stream for you today! Vault Thieves are trying to gank your Vault right out from under you. You gonna take that? Or are you gonna show 'em how sharp your teeth are?
Here they come. Light 'em up!
Get me close and I'll blast 'em!
Road block ahead!
I got you, Maya—take that next exit.
Hey hey hey! Over here! They're trapped! Tear 'em apart. For me!
We gotta get these crazies off our back before I can clear the way!
Okay, those guys, they're on fire now. Don't worry, we'll see them again at the Great Vault. Until then, make those Thieves pay for what they did to your family!

You did it, killer. It'll be a long time before Maliwan forgets the thrashing you gave 'em. Let's see the Calypsos try to spin that. Now, we've got an opening and we're gonna take it. Rhys, where's that Vault?
Get me near that entrance and I'll clear the way!
All clear! Let's move!
The Vault awaits you. / Say hi to Maya for me. / We go back a ways.
Head through the spillways!
Ohhhh, hiding in a gutter. I've always called you trash, but it's good to see you living your truth now.
I can clear the way, but we need to get these idiots off our backs first!
Get me close, and I'll clear the way!
There's the train station up ahead!
Dammit! They're already here!
That's right, you dumb shart-tarps. We've had our followers combing the city for the Vault since before you got here.

First off, I want to say a little something. You saved my skin and the skins of every Atlas employee. And skin's important! Stop saying skin. Right, the Vault. It's hidden underneath the Apollyon Transit Station.
Tch. Idiots. Did you really think you were going to beat us to it?
Don't worry, Vault Hunter. We're the ones with the Key. That Vault is ours.
Last stop, bitches!
Welcome to Apollyon Station. Where Atlas takes you farther than your dreams.
Apollyon Station welcomes you like an old friend. Hey there, bud! Lookin' good.
Apollyon Station. At the intersection of industry and transportation and luxury. It's a three-way intersection.
Apollyon Station. Try our new private transit pods. Fart up your commute in peace.
Apo... Apollyon Station. Just blast that subway car with your butt stink.
[snickering] Shh! Stop! Stop it.||Get your butt shined by our expert butt valets.
Hahahaha! Oh-ho... ho... ooh, boy. Ahahaha!
It's in the middle of the city? How did no one ever find it?
Pff, hahaha! What?! Hahahaha! S-stop! Hahahaha! Cut!
Now arriving: a bunch of dumbasses!
Passengers are encouraged to lick the third rail. Get sloppy on it!
Abababdadababab. Rutabaga watermelon. Rutabaga. Watermelon.
Dude, do your warmups BEFORE we're mic'd up.
Peter Piper picked a peck of—I'm getting a pop in my right ear. You getting that?
Let's see what you got.
Been waiting for this.
The hunt has led me to this moment.
Let's see what all the fuss is about.
Vault. Hunted.
Just as I always dreamed.
Yes. YES! This is what it means to hunt!
Holy shite! Did you see that?!
Uhhhh. What?
Kyaa? What was that?
That's a new specimen to me.
What... the actual feck.
Guardians. They protect the Vaults from anyone crazy enough to open one. They won't be happy to see us.

The old Atlas corporation just paved right over it! I found it when I took over, but I wasn't about to pop the top on that thing in a populated area. Opening a Vault is... messy stuff. But I'll leave that up to you. Rhys, out!
It's through here.
Lilith? We're in.
[static] Maya. Ava's gone! COV swarming everywhere, can't get a read.
Looks like we're on our own, Vault Hunter.
Wow. Wasn't sure I'd ever see another Vault. I'm glad you brought me back.
Imagine all the people who lived out their lives on the surface above, never knowing they were standing on top of a Vault.
Get ready. The creature the Eridians sealed inside the Vault has been sleeping for millennia. It's gonna be pissed when we wake it up.
There! That arch is the entrance. Put the key in that pedestal.
Here we go!
That... was a masterpiece of badassery! Seriously, good job.
Keep trying. Tyreen believes in you!
Hell yeah! That was awesome!
Ava? I told you to wait on the ship. It isn't safe here!
And miss a chance to see a real Vault? Look at this place!
Ava, you're not a Vault Hunter yet! There's a lot more to it than running headfirst into danger!
Right, yeah, totally.
Vault Hunter, you should go inside. Take your time. I need to have a chat with my apprentice.

Vault Hunter? Can you hear me? Do not panic! I am simply testing a new communication device based on Lilith's powers. It seems ECHO cannot penetrate the bounds of the Vault, so I am forced to use this. I am quite curious to know what you find inside.
Whatever this is, I'm into it.
Shiny.
What is this?
Alien gadget! Yesss!
That Eridian device is somehow allowing you to comprehend fourth-dimensional non-linear script. The writing doesn't technically exist, and yet it's plain as day. Please, analyze those symbols for me!
